{{History of Japan |image=Shoso-in.jpg |caption=[[Shōsōin]]}}

{{nihongo|'''Bunshō'''|文正}} was a {{nihongo|[[Japanese era name]]|年号,| ''nengō'',| lit. "year name"}} after ''[[Kanshō]]'' and before ''[[Ōnin]]''. The period spanned the years February 1466 through March 1467.<ref>Nussbaum, Louis-Frédéric. (2005). "''Bunshō''" in [https://books.google.com/books?id=p2QnPijAEmEC&pg=PA93&dq=  ''Japan encyclopedia'', p. 93;] n.b., Louis-Frédéric is pseudonym of Louis-Frédéric Nussbaum, ''see'' [https://archive.is/20120524174828/http://dispatch.opac.ddb.de/DB=4.1/PPN?PPN=128842709 Deutsche Nationalbibliothek Authority File].</ref> The reigning emperor during this period was {{nihongo|[[Emperor Go-Tsuchimikado of Japan|Go-Tsuchimikado]]''-tennō''|後土御門天皇}}.<ref>Titsingh, Isaac. (1834). [https://books.google.com/books?id=18oNAAAAIAAJ&pg=PP9&dq=nipon+o+dai+itsi+ran#PRA1-PA352,M1  ''Annales des empereurs du Japon'', pp. 352]-364.</ref>

==Change of era==
* '''1466''' {{nihongo|''Bunshō gannen''|文正元年}}: The era name was changed to mark an event or a number of events. The old era ended and a new one commenced in ''Kanshō'' 7.

==Events of the ''Bunshō'' era==
* '''1466''' (''Bunshō 1, 1st month''): ''Dainagon'' [[Ashikaga Yoshimi]], brother of the ''[[shōgun]]'' [[Ashikaga Yoshimasa]], was promoted to the second rank of the second class in the Imperial court hierarchy.<ref name="t353">Titsingh, [https://books.google.com/books?id=18oNAAAAIAAJ&pg=PP9&dq=nipon+o+dai+itsi+ran#PRA1-PA353,M1  p. 353.]</ref>
* '''1466''' (''Bunshō 1, 1st month''): [[Minamoto-no Mitsihisa]] was replaced as ''udaijin'' by ''dainagon'' [[Fuijwara no Matsatsugu]].<ref name="t353"/>

