'''Hawulti-Melazo''' (''Hawelti-Melazo'') is a [[Dʿmt|pre-Aksumite]] and [[Kingdom of Aksum|Aksumite]] archaeological site located in the northern [[Tigray Region]] in [[Ethiopia]]. It contains various old [[funerary monument]]s,<ref>{{cite book|authors=Asfawossen Asrat, Metasebia Demissie, Aberra Mogessie|title=Geotourism in Ethiopia: Archaeological and Ancient Cities, Religious and Cultural Centres : Yeha, Azum, Wukru, and Lalibela|date=2008|publisher=Shama Books|isbn=9994400304|page=67|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=foJOAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref> as well as ancient [[inscription]]s.<ref>{{cite book|author=French Centre for Ethiopian Studies|title=Dossiers: un nouveau site pre-aksumite, Mäqabér Ga'éwa. Un territoire dans l'histoire, le Lasta|date=2009|publisher=De Boccard|isbn=2701802660|page=53|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=uLvfOWnZW7MC|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref>

