'''Michael Charleston “Xiao” Briones Chua''' (born 19 January 1984) is a [[Filipino-Chinese|Chinese-Filipino]] historian,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2012/sep/24/philippines-official-imelda-marcos-shoes-have-no-h/|title=Philippines official: Imelda Marcos’ shoes have no historic value|last=http://www.washingtontimes.com|first=The Washington Times|newspaper=The Washington Times|access-date=2017-02-25|language=en-US}}</ref> academic, and television personality, best known for his academic works on [[History of the Philippines|Philippine history]] and his numerous appearances as a commentator on historical topics on [[Television in the Philippines|Philippine television]],<ref>http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/547348/lifestyle/artandculture/historian-xiao-chua-offering-free-walking-tour-in-honor-of-rizal</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blogwatch.tv/2011/11/philippine-historian-xiao-chua-says-aquino-cojuangco-video-is-propaganda/|title=Philippine historian Xiao Chua says Aquino Cojuangco video is propaganda -|date=2011-11-07|access-date=2017-02-25|language=en-US}}</ref> including a regular appearance on a news segment called "Xiao Time"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bantayog.org/?p=1073|title=Xiao Time: Ekonomiya noong Martial Law|last=|first=|date=2015-10-18|website=|language=Filipino|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> on public television station [[People's Television Network]]. He is currently a professor at [[De La Salle University]].

